	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64872139"><p>Seawater has salt and other dissolved minerals in it which make it particularly toxic. To remove these dissolved substances requires enormous amounts of energy, and as a byproduct has significant quantities of said minerals, which you then have to dispose of.</p><p>As to using pipes, well, pipes designed for transporting hydrocarbons aren't likely without massive retrofitting (read: replacing) to carry other fluids.</p><p>If you're not losing sleep over this, that's because you're an idiot, or you plan on being dead soon.</p></div>
	</div>

