		<div id="comment_body_64872225"><p>Salt disposal isn't exactly rocket science. Desalination creates a brine stream, which either goes straight back into the ocean (most common) (it has to be far enough offshore and sufficiently spread out so as to overconcentrate any location), or into evaporation ponds (less common) for mineral recovery.</p><p>Also, the current trends are increasingly favourable to desalination in the future.  The situation that we face is that solar and wind are getting incredibly cheap (and it just keeps going), but are intermit<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
