		<div id="comment_body_64872347"><p>I'll repeat: desalination is primarily electricity cost, not capital cost.  Brine discharge is a capital cost.  Proper discharge of brine - aka, NOT "wiping out coastal ecosystems", and not even having any meaningful impact (a typical desalination discharge from a large plant (tens of millions of litres per day) will have a ~5% higher salinity around 100m from the discharge point, and the discharge points are commonly hundreds of meters offshore) - is tiny compared to the cost of the electricity.</p><p>And I'll re<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

